---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SvgComponentConverter from '../../components/SvgComponentConverter.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Free SVG Component Converter - React, Vue & Svelte"
  description="Convert raw SVG markup into clean React JSX/TSX, Vue, or Svelte components locally in your browser. Preview the SVG and copy component code instantly."
>
  <SvgComponentConverter />

  <article class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-slate-200 prose max-w-none mt-4 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
    <h2 id="features" class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 border-b pb-2 border-slate-100">Why Convert SVG to Components?</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 text-sm">Componentized icons are easier to reuse, style, and pass props or attributes into. This converter supports React JSX/TSX, Vue, and Svelte while keeping everything local.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm flex flex-col gap-2">
      <li><strong>React, Vue, and Svelte:</strong> Switch between JSX, TSX, Vue template, and Svelte output.</li>
      <li><strong>Attribute Ready:</strong> Generated components spread props or framework attributes onto the root SVG.</li>
      <li><strong>Safer Preview:</strong> Script-like content is removed before rendering.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 id="faq" class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 border-b pb-2 border-slate-100">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">React output uses JSX-friendly attributes, Vue output keeps native SVG attributes with <code>v-bind="$attrs"</code>, and Svelte output spreads <code>$$props</code> on the root SVG.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
